> Political Speaker-in-waiting spent years cultivating GOP lawmakers FILE - In this Sept. 23, 2010 file photo, Rep. Kevin McCarthy, R-Calif., center, and Rep. Mike Pence, R-Ind., right, listen as then-House Minority Leader John Boehner of Ohio holds up a copy of the GOP agenda, "A Pledge to America,' at a lumber yard in Sterling, Va. McCarthy, the majority leader who’s favored to become the next speaker of the House, has energetically nurtured GOP legislators in the House since he was elected to Congress nine years ago. (AP Photo/J. Scott Applewhite, File) 
